items.text:
Hello, 
We are looking for two performers to act in a short movie. ‚ÄúWhere the Light Shines‚Äù explores denial, anxiety, and female identity in a male-dominated society. The film reflects the tension between masculine and feminine energy ‚Äì control and surrender ‚Äì and how these forces collide in the face of inner truth.
The story uses contemporary movement and dance to showcase the troubled inner-word of the characters. You will be working closely with the director and choreographer to shape the narrative.
Females, non-binary and all ethnicities is encouraged to apply!<3 This is a third year Bachelor project.  
If you are ready to move with the lights, contact us at: edsh.production@gmail.com.

Its about BLAIRs first day of being a couples councilor. Her first appointment is with a couple CHRIS and JACKIE and they are there for Chris's addiction that overwhelmed Blair.

SEEKING THE FOLLOWING ROLES

Blair ‚Äì Female 23, just received her master's degree to be a couples therapist and its her first day.

Chris ‚Äì Male 27, Active duty military, about to get deployed soon married to Jackie

Jackie - Female 24, headstrong, preppy.

items.text:
Genre: Romance/Drama

Logline: Soulmates bound from the beginning of time must navigate the blurred lines between dreams and reality to discover their destiny together.

Roles:

Atlas: 20s, Male

Atlas always feels the weight of the world on his shoulders. He understands more about life and the universe than most people, which doesn‚Äôt help his abilities to strike up a conversation and ends up making him look reserved and detached. Atlas feels everything from the rotation of the Earth to everything that is supposed to happen in the future. His connection with the world makes him patient, almost seeming like he is unable to act on his desires, because he knows what the future holds.

Luna: 20s, Female

Luna enjoys the complexities of figuring out what life is. She wants to follow her passions and figure out what they mean along the way. She isn‚Äôt the type to turn people away, but instead see what they change in her life. She is never afraid, takes her own mortality in her hands, and believes there is a right answer to everything. The spark of life is in her and she doesn‚Äôt want to let anything snuff it out. Her dreams start to show her the past and what the future holds for her.

Pierce: 20s, Male

Pierce is a constant. He is dating Luna. He never does anything unexpected. He has a very simplistic view of the world and events that occur outside of it don‚Äôt really concern him. He is steadfast in his decisions and never doubts who he is or what he is doing. You can always expect him to be around, but if things get deeper he will very quickly drown from the weight of his inexperience.

Production Company: pearscarfproductions

Writer/Director: Nathan Chelf

Cinematographer: Nate Coberly

Production Type: Independant

Contact Info: pearscarfproductions@gmail.com

Run Time: Short Film

Compensation: Negotiable, this is a low budget, self funded project.

Union Status: Non-Union

Audition Information: We will be holding in person auditions this Saturday, October 25th from 9:00 AM until 2:00 PM at 3111 E Colfax Ave Denver, CO 80206. Please email us if you are interested and we will get you a time slot. If you are unable to make it in person please reach out and we will set up a virtual audition another time or send you information to do a self tape. For in person we would love to see a monologue and we will have you do cold readings from the script.

Shooting Schedule: We are planning to be filming in December, final dates will be confirmed based on the schedules of our cast.

Filming Locations: The Denver Metro Area

Thank you for taking the time to read through this and I hope to hear from you soon!

items.text:
Til min kortfilm Banana Ice, der er st√∏ttet af Odense Filmv√¶rksted, s√∏ger jeg to kvindelige spillere til venindeparret Rikke og Sika - spillealder 19-20.

Banana Ice handler om:

Den 18-√•rige Val, der i starten af historien f√•r nedtur p√• efter hun, ved ankomst til baren, finder ud af at hendes veninder har ditchet hende. 

Men det bliver faktisk bare held-i-uheld, for hun ender med en aften p√• bar med venindeduoen Rikke og Sika.

Da de to veninder, sent p√• aftenen, g√•r ud for at spice √∏llene op og narkopolitiet kort efter kommer ind, ender Val i et dilemma.

Hun redder hendes ‚Äúnye‚Äù veninders r√∏v, men i panik og for at redde deres egen r√∏v, kaster Sika og Rikke hende under bussen.

Kortfilmen hedder som den g√∏r, fordi en vape, med den smag, er gennemg√•ende motif i historien.

Praktisk:

Kortfilmen optages i Svendborg den 29. og 30. november i dagstimerne - s√• der er selvf√∏lgelig forplejning. 

Er du og m√•ske din veninde interesseret?

S√• send en mail til majamus23@gmail.com med emnet Venindeduo_BananaIce

I mailen kunne jeg godt t√¶nke mig:

* en video af dig/jer, der som de to veninder skal f√• den sidste ved bordet til at k√∏be drikkevarer til jer - det kan f.eks. v√¶re via en l√∏gn, en leg, at stj√¶le eller noget helt andet.

* har du/I en showreel eller links til andet I har lavet, s√• send det gerne med.

* en kort, kort pr√¶sentation af dig/jer.

Her kommer lidt om veninderne:

Rikke&Sika

Sammen er de den uovervindelige venindeduo.

Man ved, ser man den ene et sted, s√• er den anden lige om hj√∏rnet.

De er det kvindelige modsvar til det heteroseksuelle forholds tosomhed.

Noget b√•de jeg og Val er misundelige p√•.

De er sp√¶ndende og fascinerende mennesker, man √∏nsker at dele en aften med.

 

Sika

Hendes for√¶ldre er succesfulde, s√• hun kommer fra et hjem hvor der bliver forventet noget af en.

K√¶rligheden er ikke ubetinget, man skal pr√¶stere og g√∏re sig umage, f√∏r man f√•r et klap p√• skulderen eller en bel√∏nning.

 

At v√¶re uartig eller opf√∏rer sig d√•rligt f√∏rer naturligvis til konsekvenser.

Sika finder nydelse i at v√¶re meget langt fra sine for√¶ldre, men hjemmet har klart givet hende en h√•rdhed.

 

Rikke

Hun har en enlig mor, inden hende og Sika blev en tosomhed, var Rikke og hendes mor det.

Hun trives godt i det kvindelige selskab og elsker f√¶llesskab og andre menneskers samv√¶r. Derfor former hun sig ogs√• meget efter de mennesker hun er sammen med, s√• hun altid passer ind og kan v√¶re en del af de sociale.

Gl√¶der mig til at se jeres mails <33

Kh Maja, manus/instrukt√∏r

Hi all! I just wanted to introduce myself and share a photos of what I look like 

I‚Äôm brand new to this and would die for some advices I want to become a actor. I can do voices and accents I can do my own stunts and fight senses. 

If anyone can point me in a direction where I can share my reals or how I could start would really appreciate it 

FYI the last photo is when I was a extra in Vera it‚Äôs why I want to do this more 

Thank you

topComments.text:
This all depends on if you want to do TV/Film or theatre.

Either way, know this.

- Yes, anyone can become an actor, however its an extremely hard industry and most never make a living from it.
- Yes, some people have become successful without training, however attending workshops and short courses will help more than you think.
- Get used to being rejected. 9/10 auditions you go for, you will probably not get. Always ask for feedback and don‚Äôt take it personally.
- students are your friends! There are so many student films/indie films out there who are crying out for actors.

Lastly, if you‚Äôre ultimately have a back up career plan! Don‚Äôt be too quick to quit the day job.

Hope this helps
Wow you were an extra in Vera, that's lush! I think it's YOU, sir, who needs to give us tips!

message.text:
If you're interested in studying at Leeds Arts University, you can find out more about our undergraduate courses at our open days in November! 

Book your place on up to three course talks, including our new courses in BA (Hons) 3D Design and Craft, BA (Hons) Creative Industries Management, BSc (Hons) Creative Technologies, and BA (Hons) Digital Marketing. 

Book your place at https://www.leeds-art.ac.uk/

Hope to see you there!

Hey there Everyone. RJ Castro,  Santa Cruz, CA.  Before I got into Acting, I was a soccer player and coach in San Jose,CA. As well as I am a Chef.

 So I like to think I can give a little Kick, and a little spice or flavor to any role you might have in mind.

 Would love to work with you. Can't wait to see you on set. Available and ready to work. Reel Credit: Produced by Sunny Creative Sunny Creative, Van Nuys, CA . 

RJ Castro
üé≠ Actor | Santa Cruz / Bay Area
IMDb: https://imdb.me/rjcastro-sj
Backstage: https://www.backstage.com/u/rjcastro-sj/
IG: https://www.instagram.com/rjcastro.sj

items.text:
*Casting Call for a short dance film shooting early next year January 24th and 25th in VANCOUVER. 
A short dance film expressing the importance of forgiveness of youth, bringing awareness to issues such as mental health, identity struggles and substance addiction in youth culture.
This is a volunteer position, but all food, studio rehearsal space and credits will be provided.
Video clips, photographs and stills will be provided as well for portfolio/demo reels to all dancers.

Requirements:
Must have contemporary dance experience and comfortable in front of camera.
Have reliable transportation to set/rehearsals
Age ranging from 19-27
Must be available BOTH shoot dates and additionally some time before the shoot for rehearsals!

DUE DATE FOR SUBMISSION: NOVEMBER 6TH 
Please submit a headshot/recent photo of yourself and a demo reel or video of your dancing.
Send all applications or questions to:
sodamihong@gmail.com 
shenassakayla@gmail.com

üé∂Offering Free VIRTUAL Voice & Acting Lessons!üé∂

Hi! I'm Colleen and I'm a music theatre voice teacher, and the owner of Virtuoso Studios. We are proud to have a team of dedicated and experienced teachers who are passionate about helping students discover the joy of music. 

We currently offer lessons in voice, piano, acting, violin, viola, cello, and guitar, along with 2 in person recitals each year in MI, WI, IL, and MO. Each of our teachers is committed to providing personalized instruction to help every student reach their goals. Whether you‚Äôre preparing for auditions, looking to grow as a performer, or simply want to enjoy making music, our teachers are here to support and encourage you every step of the way!

Try a free lesson today! This is a great way to meet one of our teachers, experience a lesson, and see how music can be a fun and meaningful part of your life.

If you‚Äôd like to get started, fill out this form, and we‚Äôll match you with the teacher who‚Äôs the best fit for your goals and interests. [www.virtuosostudios.org/free-trial-lessons](https://www.virtuosostudios.org/free-trial-lessons)

**What you‚Äôll do**

* Deliver fast ‚Äî we move quickly.

* Native or near-native German.
* Proven self-shooting experience (UGC, reels, ads, or similar).

CASTING CALL FOR A STUDENT SHORT-FILM!

Hi hi! My name is Megan Veto and I am a student at the Aurora Community College and will serve as the Writer/Director of this project. I am in need of actors/actresses for my Production 1 project! This will be unpaid, though I will provide anyone interested with a final version of the film. You will also be fed, so please let me know of any allergies or specific diets you may have!

Title: On the Rocks
Genre: Romantic Comedy
Logline: An angry bride walks into a bar and shakes up Ramos‚Äôs day.

SHOOTING DAYS: November 8th (10a - 6p) - 9th (1p - 7p)

LOCATION: 9075 E Lowry Blvd Denver, CO 80230

CHARACTERS:

-Ramos: The bartender. Late 20‚Äôs - early 30‚Äôs. Calm, cool, and collected. Takes care of his patrons. Wardrobe will be all black and a black button-up shirt.

-Sarah: The angry bride. Mid - late 20‚Äôs. Feisty, knows what she wants, but eventually softens under Ramos‚Äôs care. Please let me know what your dress size is so I can find a bride‚Äôs dress that fits! üòÅ

-Mike: The ex. Mid - 20‚Äôs. Flustered, desperately looking for Sarah. Cheated. Wardrobe will be black slacks and a nice white button-down shirt.

-Ruth: Sarah‚Äôs mom. 50‚Äôs. Helps Mike look for Sarah. Wardrobe will be a nice dress.

Please email me at megveto96@gmail.com with your headshot and demo reel, I will send you the script to read over.

Thank you so muc

Egal ob "Dogs of Berlin", "Blood Red Sky" oder dem Independenthit "HAPS", der Schauspieler Kais Setti schafft es immer wieder, an die richtig geilen Projekte zu kommen. Doch wie gelingt der Einstieg als Schauspieler? Wie kommt man die richtigen Projekte? Spannender Input:

The project will be about the exciting meeting of 2 friends outside of the prison one of them was in for two years.

I‚Äôm looking for a male actor who‚Äôd be taking the role of the friend who‚Äôs being released from jail, ideally mid - late 20‚Äôs, dark short hair (if someone here has a buzz cut that would be freakin amazing üò≠) 

It‚Äôs a really low budget project but I‚Äôd be happy to give a small symbolic payment to a talented actor who‚Äôd be engaged in telling our story üíó

We're currently casting an international actor (age 25‚Äì36) for the main role of a short film shooting between November 2‚Äì3 in Warsaw.

The story is a black comedy about David, an immigrant spending his first christmas in another country with his girlfriend's family. 

‚ùóÔ∏èRequirements: Must know another language than polish and english, must communicate well in english aswell.

This is a non-profit project, but catering and transport are provided, along with a valuable creative experience in audiovisual storytelling.

If you're interested or know someone who might be, feel free to message me for more details. Looking forward to collaborating! 

ü´∂üèªFor contact my email is : ikateon7@gmail.com

items.text:
¬∑ Title: This Side of Midnight

¬∑ Genre: Horror

¬∑ Logline: An eighteen-year-old girl must confront her inner demons, both real and metaphorical, as they test her to see if she is worthy of life itself after a brush with death.

¬∑ Role: Lilith ‚Äî Female, late teens to early 20s

A newly eighteen-year-old struggling with severe depression and suicidal thoughts. Intelligent, introspective, and haunted by her inner world. The emotional core of the story.

Note: Lead role. Must be comfortable portraying intense emotional states.

Zera ‚Äî Female, late teens to early 20s

Lilith‚Äôs best friend. Empathetic and determined, trying desperately to remind Lilith that she matters.

Dad ‚Äî Male, 40s‚Äì50s (flexible)

A concerned father trying to reconnect with his daughter after finding her following a suicide attempt. Must convey deep emotion with subtlety.

Mom ‚Äî Female, 40s‚Äì50s (flexible)

 A mother struggling to cope as her daughter begins to withdraw, stop eating, and lose hope.

Sibling ‚Äî Any gender (preferably male), 10‚Äì15 (flexible)

Appears in one scene. No speaking lines, but must express strong emotion through facial expression and presence.

Cashier ‚Äî Any gender/age

Background role, no speaking lines.

¬∑ Production Company: Cassidy Cheldelin ‚Äî Writer, Director, Videographer, Editor
Jess Lange ‚Äî Co-Director, Casting Director, Producer

¬∑ Production Type: Student Film

¬∑ Contact Information: Contact: Jess Lange ‚Äî escapemindproductions@gmail.com
Instagram: @escapemind.productions 

¬∑ Run Time: Short (16 minutes)

¬∑ Compensation: Unpaid

¬∑ Union Status: Non-Union

¬∑ Audition Information: 

Format: Digital Submission

Please record a 1‚Äì2 minute monologue of your choice (preferably horror or drama) that demonstrates emotional depth. Include your name, age, preferred email & phone number, and desired role in the email. Name, age, and role for slate. 

Lilith Auditions: Monologue may be up to 5 minutes or the attached scene from the screenplay.

Dad Auditions: May choose to perform from the attached scene.

Submit to: escapemindproductions@gmail.com
Deadline: November 5, 11:59 PM (MST)

¬∑ Shooting Schedule: Mid-November (before Thanksgiving) table read, 11/8/25 at 12 (MST), location upon casting

¬∑ Filming Location: Black Forest, CO, 80908 & Colorado Springs, CO, North Academy Blvd.

¬∑ Project Description:

Two filmmakers are passionate about exploring mental health through the lens of horror. While this is not a professional production, we approach the project with deep respect and dedication to the craft. This Side of Midnight follows Lilith as she confronts her literal demons and manifestations of her struggles with mental illness, who test her will to live. When she ultimately fails, she is tragically taken, symbolizing the devastating reality of losing the battle against one‚Äôs own mind.

Lilith and Dad Scene 

Int. BEDROOM - MORNING

The screen flickers to her dad, shaking her awake

Dad

Lilith! Wake up! Please- Please, breathe please.

Lilith sits up suddenly, her breathing is chaotic, and she is in fear.

Her dad sighs in relief

Dad

Oh, thank god you are ok. I was about to call 911. What happened??

LILITH (studdering)

I- I don't know

She looks around the room, noticing the empty pill bottle next to her pillow, and she erratically shoves it further underneath so as not to let her dad see.

LILITH

Must've just been too much melatonin..

Dad

You scared the crap out of me and you're mother. Zera too.

Lilith looks defeated as her father sits more formally on her bed.

Dad

That reminds me, you should probably call her. She was worried sick about you.

LILITH

I will- I will do that.

Dad (in relief)

Good. You missed the bus. I have to go to work n' can't drive you- so have the day off.

LiLITH (under her breath)

T-Thanks.

DAD

A mental Health day- y'know? You deserve it.

Lilith's expression doesn't change. Her dad stands up and begins to put on his jacket

DAD

Let me know if you need anything, okay?

items.text:
Hi, hello, Sat Sri Akaal, I‚Äôm Sukhmanjeet, A 16 year old aspiring actor from Australia, who will be taking a giant dive (preferably from a plane) into acting.

it should be clear that I am 16 ALTHOUGH, I have a beard, which by itself sounds very anticlimactic‚Ä¶ BUT  üôÇ‚Äç‚ÜïÔ∏è it gives me a wider range of characters to portray üòé (depending on length and gritty-ness) sometimes people mistake me as a 27 year old with my little sister as my child and it‚Äôs fun to act that out üòÖ fond memories.

I‚Äôm roughly 182 cm tall (abt 5‚Äô11 3/4), 
weigh 85 (I do plan on becoming fitter and losing weight), 
My Entinicty is south Asian/ Indian (Sikh),
Hair: black and almost shoulder length
Hair-Style: to be a wolf but as of now still growing it out ü§û
Eyes: brown
My chest size is roughly 107 cm and my hips are 97 cm

I decided to take drama classes last year, fell in love, and have focused on many different roles always pushing for roles in different projects, I‚Äôve volunteered to act in student‚Äôs film assignments just for the experience. The way I see it, every chance to act is a step closer to getting really good at what I want to do. üòÅ
 
I‚Äôm genuinly so grateful for everyone‚Äôs who have been with me, my teachers, my friends, directors and I could not be less excited to meet more amazing people such as yourself, so if your an actor, creator or a director,
Let‚Äôs connect and possibly get the chance to make something incredible together‚ÄºÔ∏è

Email: sukh.singh7t@gmail.com
Number: 0421505765
Or you could reach me here on Facebook üòÑ.

items.text:
Been cooking up a lot of projects behind the scenes and this is the most recent! 

Currently casting for a new short, working title 'The Heist', filming in Northern Quarter, Manchester!

In 1994, a duo of thieves, interrogated after a heist gone wrong, find their fates decided by the value of their mysterious stolen item ü™ô

STUDENT FILM, SHOOTING IN MANCHESTER, EARLY NOV, UNPAID

THE INTERROGATOR

mid 30s. 

Stoic but becomes fascinated with the two thieves' stories. 

RAY

20 - 30

Confident, in charge and narcissistic. Takes the lead within the duo

NICK

18 - 25

new to the crime world, scruffy and erratic. Intimidated by Ray.

Within plenty of space to collaborate, build and bring your own energy and flair to the story and the characters, this may be a good opportunity for upcoming actors building their portfolio and looking for experience! 

We are currently looking for self tape auditions

If interested please message me here or email izzyhambury1@gmail.com

for further details

items.summary:
Been cooking up a lot of projects behind the scenes and this is the most recent! 

Currently casting for a new short, working title 'The Heist', filming in Northern Quarter, Manchester!

In 1994, a duo of thieves, interrogated after a heist gone wrong, find their fates decided by the value of their mysterious stolen item ü™ô

STUDENT FILM, SHOOTING IN MANCHESTER, EARLY NOV, UNPAID

THE INTERROGATOR

mid 30s. 

Stoic but becomes fascinated with the two thieves' stories. 

RAY

20 - 30

Confident, in charge and narcissistic. Takes the lead within the duo

NICK

18 - 25

new to the crime world, scruffy and erratic. Intimidated by Ray.

Within plenty of space to collaborate, build and bring your own energy and flair to the story and the characters, this may be a good opportunity for upcoming actors building their portfolio and looking for experience! 

We are currently looking for self tape auditions

If interested please message me here or email izzyhambury1@gmail.com

for further details

Want to learn how to transition from doing music into Acting?
Or how to get your music in TV and Film? 

BBR Indie Films is thrilled to announce our Celebrity Guest  Panelist- Gary "LIL G" Jenkins! 

‚ÄãGary "LIL G" is a National Platinum Recording Artist (lead singer of the R&B super-group SILK), Producer, Songwriter, and Actor.

‚ÄãHis impressive acting credits include:
üé¨ Madea's Family Reunion (Stage Play)
üé¨ Sleepy Hollow
üé¨ Christmas Bae (coming soon)

‚ÄãDon't miss the chance to hear from a true industry veteran at our next event, we are giving all the tea. Come ready to network, we ALWAYS have several Music Supervisors in the house.

‚ÄãüìÖ Wed, October 29th, 2025
üìç Studio Movie Grill - Marietta, GA
‚è±Ô∏è 6:00 PM - 10:00 PM
üëª In the theme of Halloween. Costumes are welcomed but not required. Best Costume wins a prize.

MEET THE CAST SPAMALOT 
Next up meet patsy 
Sam has been acting practically her entire life with her first role being just 6mths. Since then she has performed in many productions, pantomimes and television over the years. Sam is also a professional singer who has toured many places since she was 16yrs old. Her fave acting parts to date have been Hayley Walker in bad dates, Truvvy in steel magnolias, Magenta in Rocky horror and Abigail Paris in the Crucibal. Sam is so excited to be performing in one of the funniest shows ever. Every rehearsal we laugh so much. Goof ball comedy at its best and this cast play the parts so well, so professionally.  It's so exciting

We are casting our one man / woman musical show Winter Wonderland that will tour care homes and community based throughout December.

items.text:
Hey there! üëãüèªüòÉ

I‚Äôm Freya Tingley ‚Äî an Australian actress born and raised in Perth. I started acting at 14, taking weekly classes with a dream of one day building a career in Hollywood.

Bit by bit, I booked short films, found a local agent, and put together a demo reel ‚Äî all steps that helped me make the leap to LA just before turning 18. Not long after, I landed my first major role as a series regular on Netflix‚Äôs Hemlock Grove, followed by Once Upon a Time, Jersey Boys, and DOTA: Dragon‚Äôs Blood.

Of course, it wasn‚Äôt all smooth sailing and the journey had its pitfalls and huge learning curves along the way. But those ups and the downs gave me something valuable; an understanding of what works, what doesn‚Äôt and the exact steps to take to keep moving forward. 

Most acting schools don‚Äôt teach how to build a career ‚Äî they‚Äôll say ‚Äúget an agent,‚Äù or ‚Äúnetwork: it‚Äôs all about who you know!‚Äù - but there‚Äôs never a clear road map, or step-by-step plan to help you to make progress, no matter where you‚Äôre at that.

I‚Äôm building a community for actors who want a clear game plan, strategy, and support to level up and turn their goals into reality.

Come hang out with us! I‚Äôd love to meet you, hear your story, and help you move closer to your dreams.

üëâ Join The Business of Acting www.skool.com/the-business-of-acting-9301/about?ref=387a46092b6b412b82c1a78a4c1a240e

See you there! üòÉ
‚Äî Freya

# CASTING CALL - PIERROT

**A UBC STUDENT SHORT FILM**

*A desperate woman on the verge of eviction, whose earnings as a sex worker mean survival, finds herself trapped in a performance of desperation and self-erasure.*

## **[MISS LEFOU]** *20 to 30 years old; all ethnicities; woman - Lead*
## [GWEN] *35 to 55 years old; all ethnicities; woman - Actor*
## [MAN] *30 to 50 years old; all ethnicities; man - Actor*

*Producer: Zev Lemke*

*Director: Julianne Pascua*
*Writer: Julianne Pascua*
*Auditions: Self-tape + In-person callback date *
*Shoot Dates: December 6-8 (3-day shoot)*
*Location: Greater Vancouver + surrounding areas*

*Callbacks: November 6th, 17:00-20:00 OR November 9th, 18:00-23:00*

**SUBMISSION DEADLINE: NOVEMBER 2ND, 2025**

**Hello, Open casting call with no experience required!**
Pierrot is a UBC short film created by students, so unfortunately, this is an unpaid position.
Given the subject matter of the script**,** we will have an intimacy coordinator on set**,** but we would also like actors who feel comfortable performing intimate scenes. 

All submissions and casting instructions can be found in the link to each casting call in the form of a GOOGLE FORM:

MSS. LEFOU - [https://forms.gle/KqgzMqHHazcWbG8UA](https://forms.gle/KqgzMqHHazcWbG8UA)

MAN - [https://forms.gle/dbEGCxoBR4KvtWb2A](https://forms.gle/dbEGCxoBR4KvtWb2A)

GWEN - [https://forms.gle/WSM1N7b7ci5gUVwo7](https://forms.gle/WSM1N7b7ci5gUVwo7)

Thank you
* Zev and the Pierrot Team

üì£üé¨ CASTING CALL - Short Period Drama 

We are casting for The Stuntman, a 3-minute period drama made as part of our final year at UWE Bristol. The film will be shot in Bristol in the week commencing 10th November 2025 (exact dates TBC). This is a student project, unpaid, but with expenses covered. The film is intended for university showcase and festival submission.

Story:
Set in 1920s Wiltshire, The Stuntman follows Ed Morris, a small-town silent cinema owner fighting to keep his theatre alive as the arrival of sound threatens to change film forever. With his fianc√©e Alice by his side, Ed stages one last ambitious stunt in the hope of saving his cinema - and their livelihood. A warm yet bittersweet drama about determination, passion and the march of technological change.

Roles:
Ed Morris (Lead, 28)
Charming, intelligent, and hardworking. Outwardly confident, but hiding a quiet desperation as he struggles to keep silent film alive. Needs strong screen presence and subtle emotional depth.

Alice Fardon (Lead, 22‚Äì23)
Ed‚Äôs fianc√©e. Feisty, loyal, and practical. She supports his dreams but occasionally shows frustration at his all-consuming determination.

Community Extras
Townsfolk gathering to watch Ed‚Äôs big stunt. A mix of ages. Families, workers and individuals. To capture the atmosphere of a 1920s local community.

Apply by: 1st November 2025
To Apply: Please send a headshot, CV (or Spotlight/Mandy link), and any showreel/self-tape to: Scarlet2.Gerry@live.uwe.ac.uk

Please include in email subject: THE STUNTMAN & NAME

items.text:
Been cooking up a lot of projects behind the scenes and this is the most recent! 

Currently casting for a new short, working title 'The Heist', filming in Northern Quarter, Manchester!

In 1994, a duo of thieves, interrogated after a heist gone wrong, find their fates decided by the value of their mysterious stolen item ü™ô

STUDENT FILM, SHOOTING IN MANCHESTER, EARLY NOV, UNPAID

THE INTERROGATOR

mid 30s. 

Stoic but becomes fascinated with the two thieves' stories. 

RAY

20 - 30

Confident, in charge and narcissistic. Takes the lead within the duo

NICK

18 - 25

new to the crime world, scruffy and erratic. Intimidated by Ray.

Within plenty of space to collaborate, build and bring your own energy and flair to the story and the characters, this may be a good opportunity for upcoming actors building their portfolio and looking for experience! 

We are currently looking for self tape auditions

If interested please message me here or email izzyhambury1@gmail.com

for further details

# (Paid) Casting for George Fox University Student Film, (Hillsboro, Oregon)

We are a group of George Fox students shooting a short film at the Airplane Home for our Location Production class, looking for a total of three non-union actors.

Project Title: Clearing The Air

Location: Airplane Home: 15270 SW Holly Hill Rd, Hillsboro, OR 97123

Safety Considerations: Dress for potential rain and cold weather. Several cats roam around the area, so be weary if you have any allergies. The actor that plays Jean will hold a non functional prop firearm.

 Shoot Dates: 10/28/2025 and 10/30/2025, 2:00PM - 9:00PM

Age Requirement: 18 and over

Pay: 50$ per day

You will receive a collection of your scenes to include in your reel.

Synopsis: Lost in the woods, siblings Gertie and Hudson come upon an airplane containing valuables. The sister aims to ransack the plane, while her brother urges her against it. Upon the return of the airplane‚Äôs resident, Jean, the sister attempts to escape with her spoils by attacking Jean from behind while her brother serves as a distraction. Her plan is thwarted by Jean, who catches her in the act, and Hudson, who reveals her presence and forces her to return what she stole. Once the two parties agree to part ways, it is revealed that Jean is a fugitive with a reward for her capture, worth more than anything the siblings could‚Äôve stolen.

Character Breakdown

(Antagonist) Jean: A perceptive older woman with a soft face but a hardened demeanor, a criminal past, and a lifetime of secrets behind her eyes.

Age: The character is meant to be in her early sixties, but her age isn't a strict guideline.

(Protagonist) Hudson: A thoughtful late teen with dark hair, an anxious posture, and a subdued retro rock styling, who has a tendency to let others walk over him.

He is the younger brother to Gertie.

"Think William Miller in Almost Famous but more frazzled and sarcastic."

Age: Roughly 18-19

(Protagonist) Gertie: An outdoorsy, has-it-all-together college girl with a ‚ÄúKaren Carpenter‚Äù fashion sense, a hidden impulsive nature, and a proclivity toward not seeing beyond her own scope.

Age: Around 20-21 years old

Audition sides are in the link below. Please record your auditions and send them to Bronson Revilla at brevilla21@georgefox.edu.

[https://docs.google.com/document/d/1JdV5_ZnMYF6723lCAGBG3bluhEtj3u9prGwzw-Q1BcY/edit?usp=sharing](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1JdV5_ZnMYF6723lCAGBG3bluhEtj3u9prGwzw-Q1BcY/edit?usp=sharing)

items.text:
**CASTING CALL ‚Äì Gaunt Man / Doctor (Dual Role) in Short Film *****The Damned Spot***

**Production Title:** *The Damned Spot*
**Company:** SWRCO Studios / Racetothefinishline Studios
**Location:** Atlanta, GA
**Union Status:** Non-Union
**Compensation:** $200 flat rate (2 half-days)
**Role: Gaunt Man / Doctor (Male, 40s‚Äì80s)**

**Character Description:**
This is a dual-performance role. The **Doctor** appears grounded, calm, and professional ‚Äî a clinician trying to reassure his patient. The **Gaunt Man** is his nightmarish double: unsettling, skeletal in presence, and haunting. The shift between the two is central to the film‚Äôs psychological horror.

**Requirements:**
* Male, age range 40‚Äì85
* Ability to portray both a grounded, realistic character and a chilling, silent presence
* Strong facial expression and physical control ‚Äî much of the horror relies on stillness and presence
* Comfortable with light makeup (pale complexion, under-eye work) and basic VFX markers
**Filming Commitment:**
* 2 Half-Days
* $200 flat rate
**To Apply:**

Please submit:
* Headshot and resume (or reel, if available)
* Brief note about prior experience in psychological drama or horror
* Contact information

Send submissions to: **studio@swrco.us**
**Deadline:** **10-24-2025**
